# BLIT386 API names in demos

Demos call the library through `BT` and `configure()` — use the **same public names** as blit386.

Canonical references (read before adding or renaming API usage):

- [blit386/CLAUDE.md](https://github.com/blit386/blit386/blob/main/CLAUDE.md) — **Boolean naming**, **BT API: getters vs
  methods**, **Input conventions**
- [blit386/docs/developer-experience-guide.md](https://github.com/blit386/blit386/blob/main/docs/developer-experience-guide.md)
  — full three-tier boolean table
- [input guide](https://blit386.dev/docs/guides/input) — input examples

## Configure flags (Tier B)

Use grammatical `is*` names from `HardwareSettings`:

- `isOverlayEnabled`, `isOverlayVisibleAtStart`, `isOverlayToggleHintVisible`, `isOverlayToggleEnabled`
- `isOverlayPaletteEnabled`, `isOverlayTimingChartEnabled`, `isOverlayRendererDiagnosticsBarEnabled`
- `isDetectingDroppedFrames`, `isWaitingForDOMReady`
- `canvasID`, `containerID` in bootstrap options (not `canvasId`)

## Input on `BT` (Tier A)

- Hold: `BT.isDown(...)`, `BT.isKeyDown(...)`
- Edge: `BT.isPressed(...)`, `BT.isReleased(...)`, `BT.isKeyPressed(...)`, `BT.isKeyReleased(...)`
- Pointer: `BT.isPointerActive(slot?)`

Do not use removed names: `BT.isButtonDown` (use `BT.isDown`), unprefixed `isKeyDown` / `isKeyPressed` (use
`BT.isKeyDown` / `BT.isKeyPressed`), `overlayEnabled` (use `isOverlayEnabled`), `canvasId` (use `canvasID`).

## When the library API changes

Update affected demo `configure()` blocks, runtime call sites, this repo's `CLAUDE.md`, and `README.md` in the same
change.
